Package: riftchat
Version: __VERSION__
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: rift-shared (>= 0.2.0), python3 (>= 3.11), curl
Recommends: i2pd
Maintainer: Rift Maintainers <ops@rift.pw>
Homepage: https://rift.pw
Description: RiftChat - Reticulum mesh messenger
 RiftChat is a Reticulum-native messenger that works without the internet.
 Messages travel over LoRa radio, BLE, WiFi-Direct, Ethernet, or the public
 internet - whichever Reticulum transports are available.
 .
 Wire-compatible with Sideband, NomadNet, and other LXMF clients.
 Memory for the Mesh.
 .
 Installs on both amd64 and arm64 (Architecture: all). Native dependencies
 (rns, lxmf, aiohttp, peewee, cryptography, …) come pre-resolved from the
 shared /usr/lib/rift/venv owned by the rift-shared package — no per-arch
 build at install time.
 .
 MIT-licensed. Full attribution and upstream credit in
 /usr/share/doc/riftchat/copyright.
